fields.name: Stock
fields.description: Ownership in a company, providing potential dividends and price appreciation.

fields.name: Bond
fields.description: Debt securities that pay interest and return the principal at maturity.

fields.name: Equity Fund
fields.description: Investment funds that primarily invest in stocks, aiming for capital appreciation.

fields.name: Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT)
fields.description: Funds that invest in real estate, generating income through rents and property sales.

fields.name: Fixed Income Fund
fields.description: Funds that invest in debt securities, providing steady income with lower risk.

fields.name: Multimarket Fund
fields.description: Funds that invest in a variety of asset classes, including stocks, bonds, and derivatives.

fields.name: Currency (Forex)
fields.description: Market for trading national currencies, profiting from exchange rate changes.

fields.name: Cryptocurrency
fields.description: Digital currencies using cryptography, traded on decentralized networks.

fields.name: Certificate of Deposit (CDs)
fields.description: Time deposits with banks, offering interest and returning principal at maturity.
